cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-person interaction recognition from video data. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video data and proposes a fusion network to improve recognition accuracy. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses a long short-term memory (LSTM) model to consider the temporal dynamics of the video. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is possible as the paper deals with recognizing human interactions from a first-person viewpoint. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also possible as the paper deals with camera ego-motion, which is relevant to robotics applications.
